      <hedline>
        <hl1>Germ-Free Flying</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Deloris St John letter on June 25 articles about flying notes she and her husband don allergy-germ masks aboard planes (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Your informative collection of articles about flying, ''We Hope You Enjoy Your Flight,'' (June 25) greeted my husband and me as we returned from our trip to Europe on Air France in ''compact class,'' otherwise known as coach.</p>
        <p>One item we would not board the plane without, in any class, is our allergy-germ masks. They are available in pharmacies. We always wear them while sleeping and during most of the flight.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: Your informative collection of articles about flying, ''We Hope You Enjoy Your Flight,'' (June 25) greeted my husband and me as we returned from our trip to Europe on Air France in ''compact class,'' otherwise known as coach.</p>
        <p>One item we would not board the plane without, in any class, is our allergy-germ masks. They are available in pharmacies. We always wear them while sleeping and during most of the flight.</p>
        <p>We ignore the startled looks of the other passengers, and after people sneeze and cough, we get looks of envy.</p>
        <p>DELORIS ST. JOHN  Laguna Niguel, Calif.</p>
      </block>
